[00:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hi, I\'m Hoon, co-founder of Beeble an AI&nbsp;VFX platform for professionals. Today, we\'re launching Canvas, your ultimate AI compositor. Canvas is a next generation&nbsp;compositing tool that lets you create&nbsp;high-end&nbsp; video content at the speed of AI.'

[00:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s built for filmmakers, VFX&nbsp; artists, post-production houses, agencies, content creators, and video editors for anyone who needs this&nbsp; type&nbsp;of high-end content.'

[00:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Let\'s take a look. In Canvas, you can access our signature AI models SwitchX&nbsp;for generative compositing and VFX Pass Generator powered by SwitchLight. Isolate subjects with AI&nbsp;rotoscoping by simply selecting what you want to keep.'

[00:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Then perfect your matte using&nbsp; Erode/Dilate,&nbsp;Invert and Merge Alpha. Generate video and image assets&nbsp; using Seedance, Kling, Happy Horse, Nano Banana, GPT-2 and Flux all in our Canvas.'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We also have special AI nodes such as&nbsp; Camera&nbsp;Angle Edit, Depth Anything, and LLM. Here we have essential edit&nbsp; nodes for hybrid compositing.'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Complete your shot with Trim,&nbsp; Extract Frame, Curves, Blur, Paint, Crop, Channels, and Merge nodes. And the Compositor node enables you to do&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'layer-based editing, kind&nbsp; of like mini After&nbsp;Effects. Place your background plate and&nbsp; rotoscope videos on top of each other wherever&nbsp;you want to control&nbsp; your scene composition. Now, let\'s see canvas in action.'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is a standard&nbsp;multicam green screen scenario. Traditionally, this requires tedious rotoscoping and complex&nbsp;3D camera tracking. Let\'s see how canvas handles&nbsp; them with AI first workflow. Our strategy for&nbsp;camera tracking is running SwitchX twice.'

[01:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'First, to include the markers in the background&nbsp; for tracking and second to erase them. And for scene continuity, We\'ll adapt one reference image for both&nbsp; angles using the QWEN Camera Angle node. Let\'s dive in.'

[02:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We start with these two shots. We&nbsp;extract our video matte intentionally keeping the tracking markers. To build our environment, we&nbsp; generate a concept with nano banana. For scene continuity, we rotate this concept image'

[02:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'using the camera angle node to match both shots. Then enhance the realism with GPT Image 2. Now we run the first shot through SwitchX. Thanks to the markers in our matte,'

[02:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'SwitchX uses&nbsp;them as a context to generate&nbsp; a background with seamless&nbsp; natural camera movement. To erase&nbsp;these markers, we run SwitchX again using a loose inverted alpha mask. A loose mask helps&nbsp;SwitchX inpaint much better,'

[02:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'giving us a clean, beautiful final shot. Repeat this process for&nbsp;the second shot and connect both clips into the compositor node to arrange and preview our&nbsp;complete scene on a single timeline.'

[03:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And that\'s it. This is just the beginning. We\'ll constantly&nbsp;add new nodes, workflows, tutorials, and templates for the pros. Thanks for watching'

[03:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and we can\'t&nbsp;wait to see what you will create with Canvas.'
